class Solution {
public:
    long long waysToBuyPensPencils(int total, int cost1, int cost2) {
        long long ans = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i <= total / cost1; i++) {
            ans += (total - i * cost1) / cost2 + 1;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(total/cost1)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution uses a single loop to iterate over the possible number of pens, and for each number of pens, it calculates the possible number of pencils that can be bought with the remaining money, adding 1 to account for the case where no pencils are bought.

